name: Walmart
directions: Straight in the back of the store, in the shoe department
comment: There is a family restroom in the back, single stall room

name: The Dish
directions: In the back, just to the right after going in the door
comment: Small diner. Can get cramped during lunch rush

name: Biggby coffee
directions: Directly to the right of the counter just past the whole bean coffee display.
comment:
Just let us know that you are just here to use the bathroom. Particularly at night, because that means we can go back to our duties as opposed to waiting by the register to make sure you get served. We promise we won't be mad that you didn't buy anything, we are happy to help you feel safe, use our bathrooms anytime :)
Also both are handicap accessible and both bathrooms have changing tables

name: Target
directions: Family Restroom close to the entrance

name: Laredo Medical Center
directions: 2nd floor by ICU

name: Case Residence Hall
directions: 1st (ground) floor. North and South sides of building right next to cafeteria entrances.
comment:
Residence halls closed to public after 12 pm.
A hot air dryer, no paper towel.

name: duckduck
directions: Back left corner.
comment: Single stall, BUT no lock. Sign telling you how little they care there's no lock. Have someone hold the door shut if possible.

name: Sadleir House
directions: on the main floor, beside the lecture hall.

name: Talize
directions: Inside the change room area, located at the back right corner of the store

name: Dancing Blueberries
directions: Near the back of the restaurants
comment: Must be a paying customer

name: Otonabee College
directions: Beside the women's washroom, near Wenjack theatre, down a hallway just past the vending machines.

name: WREC Center
directions: First floor across from elevator
comment: Family Restroom

name: CSU, CHICO Student Health Center
directions: First floor, ask for family restroom at Acute Care Desk. Second floor, ask Nurse’s Station.
comment: These restrooms are generally reserved for faculty and staff only, but may be requested by students.

name: CSU, Chico Student Housing Office
directions: Ask at the counter for an accessible or family restroom

name: Center for Continuing Education
directions: Inside next to stairs, enter southeast door.

name: Cafe In The Park
directions: Past the tills in the cafe (in Rickmansworth Aquadrome)
comment: Two single stalls, one with boxers on the front, the other with knickers, no need to be a paying customer it a very relaxed, friendly cafe

name: The Banshee
comment: This is a bar and pub, open to all ages before 9pm. There is a gendered single occupancy restroom as well as a gender inclusive single occupancy restroom.

name: Target
directions: "Family" restroom immediately to the left of the entrance, before you reach the traditional multi-stall gendered facilities.

name: Jo-Ann Fabrics
directions: In the back left of the store - you have to walk through/past the jewelry section and a lot of art supplies. Restrooms are single-stall, recently converted from gendered facilities, so the one in the back still has a urinal.

name: Target
directions: It's a family restroom right near the men/woman restrooms

name: 825 Northeast Multnomah Street, Portland, OR 97232, USA
directions: enter lobby, make a right at the front desk, pass elevators, immediate right before the atm. pass 2 gendered restrooms. its the thirs one on the right.
comment: public bathroom for the whole building. i work across the street and come here during the day to use the bathroom.

name: Bikes@Vienna
directions: In the rear of the mechanics area, also another in the back room but not available in winter due to cold.
comment: Just ask to use the bathroom and one of the employees will point you in the direction. There is a step down when entering so not wheelchair friendly.

name: Library Computer Lab - Pacific Union College
directions: ADA accessible (on the left-hand side when facing the south wall the the computer lab, computer lab located behind the library reference desk) - campus map building number 28

name: Target
directions: Next to the pharmacy.
comment: There's a single stall unisex bathroom next to the pharmacy

name: Clark Hall - Pacific Union College
directions: ADA accessible from the back entrance (on the right hand side of the hallway) - campus map building number 40

name: Moan and Dove
directions: 2 gender neutral bathrooms, front one is handicap accesible
comment: paying customers only, 21+

name: Mudpie Vegan Coffee House
directions: First floor, left past the counter
comment: Open to anyone, you don't have to be a customer.

name: Dining Commons - Pacific Union College
directions: ADA accessible (in the main entrance lobby immediately to the left upon entering) - campus map building number 26

name: Railtown Cafe
directions: To the right of the till.
comment: Probably need to buy something, but if it is busy in the cafe, you probably won't even be noticed.

name: USCB Hilton Head Gateway Campus, 65 University Boulevard, Okatie, SC 29909, USA
directions: Second floor in library.
comment: Not many people use it

name: Chipotle Mexican Grill
directions: Top floor by the stairs

name: Dangerously Delicious Pies
directions: In back, up ramp. 3 gender neutral restrooms
comment: paying customers only

name: 1911 Building
directions: Third floor, north side, two neutral single-stall bathrooms on left.
comment: If you're not a student, closed on weekends.

name: Starbucks
directions: Go in and it's in the back to right of counter.
comment: You probably need to pay for something but if you do they are pretty chill and let people hang out either inside or outside.

name: Oak Lawn Coffee
directions: Inside to the left in a small hallway area before internal door to dog grooming place.
comment: Generally friendly, staff will see you come in so not super private.

name: Jefferson People's House
comment: They're super friendly and awesome and even if you aren't a paying customer I have no doubt they will let you use their restroom. But you should buy their toast because it's delicious.

name: Glassfabriken
directions: Anarchist café, walk into the back of the main room and you will find a single stall non-gendered restroom.
comment: Free of charge and you don't need to buy anything to use the restroom.

name: Publix
directions: Bathrooms are to the left when you enter the store.
comment: Too much traffic for associates to care if you're a customer. There's a family restroom under construction that faces the cashiers, and there's a short hallway that takes you to the doors for the gendered stalls.

name: Starbucks
directions: Two doors to the building, one on the same side as Subway, one on the same side as a frozen yogurt place. Enter by the frozen yogurt place and they're about 12 feet in, and to the left. Generally the line forms toward that door. Two gendered single stalls.
comment: I haven't tried "hit and run" peeing but the doors are open and the baristas don't seem to be focused on who is entering/exiting the bathrooms (the bar actually faces the door on the Subway side, not the door closest to the bathrooms)

name: The Cocktail Shack
directions: Through the bar, down the stairs, small door straight ahead.
comment: Small, trendy cocktail bar. WC is self contained room with sink etc.

name: Club Revenge
directions: first floor, in hallway off the stairwell - mens at one end, unisex at the other. Consisting of about 10 stalls.
comment: This is not a particularly trans inclusive gay club, but the toilets are unisex.

name: Presuming Ed's
directions: Through double swing doors toward the back of the building.
comment: Very chilled out place, great coffee and cake, bathroom consists of two separate locking stalls.

name: Emporium
directions: near entrance, to the right

name: Atheneos Greek Village Cafe
directions: Around the left side of restaurant towards the back.
comment: You would probably need to buy food, they do takeout as well as delivery, slightly public location.

name: Funhouse Lounge
comment: Bar, but all ages. Requires being a paying customer.

name: Mario's Fine Menswear
directions: In the back of store.
comment: Just ask employees to use the restroom.

name: Sogni di Dolci
directions: At the back of the cafe/restaurant. Down the hallway on the right side. Two safe bathrooms.

name: Subway
directions: There are two lockable single-toilet restrooms and the doors with gender markers are both behind one door in the back of the dining area. Those who use it need not be paying customers.

name: Starbucks
directions: Around the left corner of the counter

name: Child and Family Services
directions: Third floor unisex accessible bathroom

name: Foster City Dog Park
directions: By parking lot entrance
comment: Free and open, hours unlocked roughly dawn to dusk.

name: Booksamillion
directions: Go to the left exit sign, door on the right is gender neutral.
comment: You don't have to be a customer to use the restrooms

name: Lan Larb
comment: Great Thai food, and they don't care which bathroom you use.

name: Starbucks
directions: Back of the store
comment: Employees are all very nice, I have used my preferred bathroom multiple times and never had an issue.

name: Starbucks
comment: Just ask where the bathrooms are because it's a bit confusing when your not around this area since its a university based Starbucks!! - generally people don't know where it is. Just ask!! There is a Single Unisex bathroom there when you find the way to the restroom it's the last one at the end when you walk past the Men's room staring right in front of you.

name: Johnson & Wales University - Wales Hall
directions: Ground floor: walk pass the fitness center and mini lounge next to the weight room.
comment: Two single unisex bathrooms.

name: Frankel's Costume Company Inc.
directions: Next to the theatrical makeup department.

name: VCU Wellness Resource Center (The Well)
directions: Single stall restrooms on all three floors.
comment: Tell front desk staff you need to use the restroom, they will direct you to it.

name: Jackson Park Health Centre
directions: Main floor to left of food court.
comment: parking is a pay lot. Generally open from 8-430. Usually low volume

name: Duncan, BC/Subway restaurant
comment: Pair of gender-neutral single-stall washrooms

name: Apple Store, San Francisco
directions: First floor, in the back, on the right.
comment: Store staff has no problem with public restroom use.

name: Panther Coffee
directions: Just inside the door, to the right, near the cashiers.
comment: probably a good idea to be a paying customer. This is a busy/high-traffic business.

name: monks house of ale repute
directions: First door on right coed restroom

name: Nebraska State Office Building
directions: Third floor, between the northwestern most elevator door (there are four elevator doors) and the Commission for the Blind office.
comment: Marked with "Restroom" and the standard wheelchair image.  Gender neutral single-person restroom.  Includes a toilet, sink, urinal, and infant changing table.

name: Meijer Gas Station
directions: At the Gas Station

name: Community College of Philadelphia, West Building
directions: On second floor, just past the entries to the binary-gendered bathrooms. It is explicitly marked as a single occupancy all-gender bathroom.
comment: You will need to swipe a CCP ID card after 5pm to enter the building

name: Theaterhaus Mitte Berlin
directions: 1st floor, turn right
comment: only the toilet on the first floor is unisex. free, but be discreet

name: Target
directions: Just inside main entrance, on left.
comment: Separate single-occupancy unisex restroom, near standard multi-occupancy gendered restrooms and water fountain.

name: Near Bikini Red
directions: From Warner St near Bikini Red, walk between the buildings towards the middle of the square/block and toilets are on the right.
comment: 2 unisex toilets available, one accessible. Not always open - best guess is during business hours when the nearby food places are open.

name: Brisbane Square Library
directions: Unisex toilets are available on the first and second floors.

name: UTC Library
directions: It's in the New Library right outside of the Starbucks!
comment: I believe the library is open to the public, but it wouldn't be hard to look like a student. Also, UTC has two more on the way!

name: Teaching and Learning Center - Pacific Union College
directions: Restroom off the main lobby on the right, just before the entrance to the Great Room classroom.
comment: Service details and learning center hours - http://www.puc.edu/academics/tlc/home.

name: Gilwoods Cafe
directions: Two gender neutral restrooms just past the register on the left hand side.
comment: This is a great locals restaurant. A wonderful place for breakfast or lunch. Check out the community table (a place to choose a chair and eat with others) just inside the front door.

name: Fisher Hall - Pacific Union College
directions: First floor entrance under the stairs.

name: terrain
directions: Toward the right in the back, near the restaurant counter. There are 3, maybe 4 single occupant bathrooms labelled with generic man/woman/handicapped symbols above the doors.
comment: Bathrooms are for customers, not public restrooms, so you may want to browse a little. Nice stuff there, 'tho expensive.

name: Liverpool Guild Sphinx Bar
directions: Back of Sphinx Bar
comment: Should be able to use regardless, many students go in and out without paying for anything

name: Monster Ronson's Ichiban Karaoke
directions: Past the bar & karaoke booths there are three signs, for boys, girls and "not sure".
comment: There's a cover charge if there are events, but usually you can just walk in and pretend you're meeting friends in one of the karaoke boxes. If you're feeling extroverted you might really meet new friends!

name: Neu West Berlin
directions: After the entrance there's a corridor and it's on the left hand side.

name: Red Rattler Theatre
directions: At back of theatre, at either side of the stage. Additional non accessible stalls upstairs.
comment: Queer run venue. On nights with 'straight' events, people may gender the toilets

name: Public toilets
directions: http://www.cityofsydney.nsw.gov.au/explore/facilities/public-toilets
comment: Coin operated free standing public toilets throughout central city area.

name: The Bearded Tit
directions: To the right of the bar, door on the left
comment: Queer run bar. Sign on toilet door "no assumptions, no gender roles, just toilets"

name: Leaf Teahouse
directions: First floor in the back.
comment: The owner, Susan, is super chill and a strong ally. She'd let anyone use the bathroom.

name: Golden Lotus
directions: In the secondary chamber of the restaurant which is straight ahead when you enter. The bathroom is then to the right.
comment: You should buy some food. They have delicious veggie meat substitutes!

name: The Lutheran School of Theology at Chicago
directions: One All Gender restroom on third floor right across from elevator. Second All Gender bathroom in Library. Third All Gender bathroom on second floor, north wing of building.
comment: The second floor restrooms (any and all genders) are a little hidden due to the construction of the building, but everyone is friendly and willing to give directions.

name: all souls unitarian universalist
directions: First floor back of room.
comment: Hours vary.

name: The Drawing Center
directions: two unisex single-stall bathrooms. downstairs behind the reception desk, there are stairs and an elevator.
comment: admission into the further-back main part of the gallery is $5, but I believe you could browse their book area (in the reception lobby) for a bit or just come in and ask about information/hours etc, and then ask to use the bathroom, and they wouldn't give you any grief about not paying.

name: Crossroads Mall
directions: Right next to the food court entrance to the mall.
comment: It is a "Family Restroom".
